  "title": "Associate Engineer (Fabs Operation / 12-hours shift)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Operate multiple type of semiconductor equipment in cleanroom environment based on process specifications. </li><li>Ability to use computer-based programs and applications to perform daily work/duties.</li><li>Participate actively and be responsible in assigned on-the-job assignments and other required trainings when requested.</li><li>Monitor performance, timely communication with Engineers-in-charge to perform equipment errors recovery promptly when necessary.</li><li>Demonstrate excellent teamwork to promptly execute process sequences and data collections if required.</li><li>Always follow safety protocols & rules in the Clean Room.</li><li>Ensure 6S in the work environment and promptly report hazards/ suspicious/ abnormal activities or personnel if any identified.</li><li>Address potential areas for improvements such as wafers processing cycle time, Equipment utilization, Safety/ Compliances, and cost savings.</li><li>Provide machine operations coverage and backup supports when necessary.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Microelectronics/Electrical/Mechanical/Chemical Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>Understanding of semiconductor process - at least 1-3 years of experience in semiconductor processes (Photolithography, Dry/Wet Etch/Cleans, Thin Films, Diffusions, Chemical mechanical Polishing, Metrology, etc.)</li><li>Able to perform independently yet working in a team. </li></ul><p><br />GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd | EA Licence 11C3793 | EA Personnel: Novita Widjaja | Registration No: R22105960</p><p><em>This is in partnership with the Employment and Employability Institute Pte Ltd (e2i).</em></p><p><em>e2i is the empowering network for workers and employers seeking employment and employability solutions. e2i serves as a bridge between workers and employers, connecting with workers to offer job security through job-matching, career guidance and skills upgrading services, and partnering employers to address their manpower needs through recruitment, training, and job redesign solutions. e2i is a tripartite initiative of the National Trades Union Congress set up to support nation-wide manpower and skills upgrading initiatives.</em></p><p><em>By applying for this role, you consent to GMP Recruitment Services (S) Pte Ltds </em><a href=\"https://www.gmprecruit.com/legal/privacy-policy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>PDPA</em></a><em> and </em><a href=\"https://us-west-2.protection.sophos.com/?d=e2i.com.sg&u=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZTJpLmNvbS5zZy9wZHBhLw==&i=NThlNDdhOGMyYmI5N2YwZmQxZDk4NjQw&t=cWdqRFV0Uy80RjN3MDlSYmM1dS85VTRxVTRoYVlXdWFyWTYzaGlVS3k0TT0=&h=1ad0460f503340658fbeab159c31256f&s=AVNPUEhUT0NFTkNSWVBUSVaVGQEVMuPAipiPENS4aadnRg3RqoiWpHBKgNtumWhHjA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>e2is PDPA</em></a><em>.</em></p>",
